x_n \to \infty 
x_n f(x_n ) \geq \varepsilon
\frac{\varepsilon}{x_n}\leq f(x_n) \implies \sum_{n\in\mathbb{N}}\frac{\varepsilon}{x_n} \leq  \sum_{n\in\mathbb{N}} f(x_n) \leq \int_0^1 f(x)dx.
